        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} is a 57-year-old man from the Czech Republic who comes in because of gradually worsening knee pain and stiffness consistent with gonarthrosis, with discomfort that is most noticeable during walking, climbing stairs, and after longer periods of activity; the presentation is kept focused on common mechanical joint symptoms because the supplied evidence does not describe unusual knee findings and specifically notes that rare or atypical symptoms should be considered only when supported [PMID:34991369]. He has a slight antalgic gait and prefers to sit with the affected knee extended when waiting in the clinic. He says the pain has slowly begun to limit his daily routines, and he has cut back on recreational walking.\n\nHe works a practical, physically active job in building maintenance, spending much of the day on his feet. Outside work, {patientName} enjoys weekend trips with his wife, light gardening, and meeting friends at a local pub. He lives with his spouse, and his adult daughter visits often. He is frustrated that knee discomfort now makes it harder to keep up with family activities.\n\nIn appearance, {patientName} is overweight and otherwise well appearing, with no signs suggesting an acute infection or systemic illness; this restrained description reflects the fact that the provided evidence does not support inflammatory, infectious, or upper-respiratory features for this case [PMID:32913861, PMID:34991369]. He describes pain as deep and aching, with brief morning stiffness and worsening after use, and says he sometimes hears or feels grinding in the knee during movement.\n\nHe has been trying to manage the pain by pacing activities, taking over-the-counter analgesics, and avoiding long walks. He is seeking help now because the symptoms are interfering with sleep after busy workdays and because he worries about losing mobility and independence."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "fullUrl": "urn:uuid:21a85dbf-4830-4af5-be1f-1954a26bbd70",
      "resource": {
        "resourceType": "Communication",
